column5: Mother nature is being cruel this weekend so far. High winds, and when winds get down, she decided to make it wet. 2 hours covered in 2 minutes  I had to try, thats the way I roll.
That's one fish more than I caught today Brian! You've got a great set up there btw.
And Monday looks like a carbon copy. Yet look at Tuesday. Back to work and winds die right off here. Of course. LOL  Thanks
Got out for an hour yesterday. Heard today the walleye are closer to shore. Now I'm watching the rain fall.
Got out for an hour yesterday. Heard today the walleye are closer to shore. Now I'm watching the rain fall.   They always are Jer.  Might head up next weekend.
One of the neighbours has said it's been good. Hoping tomorrow morning I get out. Let me know how you do.
Winds were high yesterday and today. Hasn't stopped raining all day either.  Hopefully tomorrow is okay. Haven't found any fish lol. Lots of boats out though.
work then rain's been getting in my way!  I'm going to try a covered spot tomorrow if it's raining.
you r just hard core lol

Pretty cool there Brian! Do you think an old fat boy could manage to get out in one of them rigs? I have been looking at kayaks and stuff, but really can't see myself being agile enough to do it. Nice to see the Go Pro videos as well! Excellent job!
